John Ameh, Abuja The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd. ), on Wednesday   inaugurated Mrs Folasade Yemi-Esan as the Head of Civil Service of the Federation. The ceremony took place at the Executive Council Chambers of the State House around11.07am when the oath was administered on the new HoS. Yemi-Esan was first appointed in acting capacity by the President in September 2019. Yemi-Esan succeeded Mrs Winifred Oyo-Ita, who’s retirement, Buhari approved last week. Copyright PUNCH.
